page: Social class in the United States
message:
Removed ambiguity, thus: there is a difference between a widespread cultural belief in a universal three-class social system on the one hand, and on the other a widespread cultural belief that in one's own culture there exist just three classes consisting of the rich, the poor and those in between.  No citation is given here to support either (dubious?) assertion. The second assertion would seem to be that intended here — not that it is necessarily true.
